From e0c52309e8380b33239b16a85fbedb5da7d12675 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: dwhinham <dale@dalewh.inham.org.uk>
Date: Tue, 28 Oct 2025 19:05:25 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 2/4] wifi: ath12k: Always disable rfkill for Surface Pro 11

On UEFI ARM64 systems (Surface Pro 11), the firmware provides the
devicetree and we cannot add a "disable-rfkill" property to it.
Unconditionally skip rfkill configuration so WiFi works out of the box.

Original patch checked devicetree property; this version just returns 0.
---
 drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/core.c | 3 +++
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+)

diff --git a/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/core.c b/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/core.c
index 5d494c5cdc0da3..954028495ea6a1 100644
--- a/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/core.c
+++ b/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/core.c
@@ -78,6 +78,9 @@ static int ath12k_core_rfkill_config(struct ath12k_base *ab)
 	if (ath12k_acpi_get_disable_rfkill(ab))
 		return 0;

+	/* Surface Pro 11: rfkill is hard-blocked by firmware, skip it */
+	return 0;
+
 	for (i = 0; i < ab->num_radios; i++) {
 		ar = ab->pdevs[i].ar;

--
2.48.1
